## Description

Shift handover notes allow operators and supervisors to record end-of-shift observations linked to a specific line and job. These notes provide continuity between shifts and are visible to all team members as read-only records after 48 hours. 

## Fields

| field      | label         | type     | required | default | validation | notes |
| ---------- | ------------- | -------- | -------- | ------- | ---------- | ----- |
| handoverId | Handover ID   | number   | yes      | —       | —          | Auto-generated primary key |
| lineId     | Line          | number   | yes      | —       | —          | Must reference an existing line |
| jobId      | Job           | number   | yes      | —       | —          | Must reference an existing job |
| notes      | Notes         | string   | yes      | —       | max 2000 chars | Free-text shift observations |
| createdBy  | Created By    | string   | yes      | —       | —          | Username of the creating operator/supervisor |
| createdAt  | Created At    | datetime | yes      | now     | —          | Timestamp of creation; system-assigned |

## Business rules

- Notes are required; a handover record cannot be saved without them.
- Only users with the Operator or Supervisor role can create or edit handover records.
- Records become read-only 24 hours after creation; no further edits are permitted.
- A handover record must be linked to a valid, existing line and job.

> [!warning] Edge cases
> - If the referenced job is closed before the 24-hour window expires, the record is still editable until the 24-hour limit.

> [!question] Open questions
> - [ ] Should supervisors be able to edit records beyond 24h in exceptional circumstances, or is the lock absolute?

